Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.54,0:00:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Well you certainly have found an excellent piece of property
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a 20 minute drive to the center of Berlin perfectly situated in a convenient and love
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.80,0:00:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovely neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.85,0:00:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rare to find a unique property of such caliber especially on the east side
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.71,0:00:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I Can Only Imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken wasn't this the residents of Mr Liebert the former head of Commerce of East Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how buyer you just came to investigate Mr Liebert is that all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.35,0:00:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me but I just need some information
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.22,0:00:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about an official who died almost 10 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.57,0:00:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently Mr Liebert and his wife adopted fraternal twins during the time that they were here I told you I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything well who owns the property
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.04,0:00:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you direct me to them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.58,0:01:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen a lot of the property in former East Germany used to be owned by Jews who had to flee during the Nazi regime
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.49,0:01:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In some cases the government ended up borrowing land from people on the west side or in other countries
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.63,0:01:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The owner of this property is overseas
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.94,0:01:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.22,0:01:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My company is a Westside real estate firm that entered the Eastern Market after the wall hell
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know anything about the past now if you could please hurry and leave I'm locking up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.71,0:01:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anyone who might remember
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.76,0:01:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Could there possibly be someone who knew the leverts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.58,0:01:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I already told you this was a residential area where many high-ranking officials live
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.95,0:01:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them fled soon after the wall came down
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.77,0:01:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially the officials from the ministry of the interior
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.40,0:01:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.19,0:01:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An ex-official from the East German Department of Commerce lives about 10 houses away
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.85,0:01:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah I remember Mr Liebert
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never understand why you decided to take such a risk if only he had waited just a little longer until East Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:01:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Collapsed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.83,0:02:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder why you went to a free country only to be killed in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.18,0:02:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a damn shame really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember if Mr Liebert had children twins perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.56,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he have twins you say
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.17,0:02:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.47,0:02:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr Liebert adopted those twins from The Orphanage are you sure
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.57,0:02:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right those two are such cute kids
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.38,0:02:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr Liebert always did talk about wanting children
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.71,0:02:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Which orphanage was it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.76,0:02:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one was it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,511
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.39,0:02:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes that's right I believe they came from 511 kinderheim
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.26,0:02:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.79,0:02:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,511 kinderheim
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're planning on turning this old orphanage into a supermarket sometime soon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,About time thank goodness they're finally going to destroy this creepy building
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me ma'am by any chance do you know anyone from this place
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.55,0:05:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone from there is long since gone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.37,0:05:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I really prefer not to talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.51,0:05:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I if you want to find out more about it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.58,0:06:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a former official from the old Ministry of welfare named Hartman over on 47th Street
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.42,0:06:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.70,0:06:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know if a man named Hartman lives around here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.35,0:06:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait what's wrong you're injured
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.17,0:06:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.98,0:06:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be afraid I'm not going to hurt you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You reinjured an old wound
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's infected but this should help
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Attaboy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.99,0:06:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this stings but it'll help you get better
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go all done
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.61,0:07:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful okay
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You might get hurt again
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.08,0:07:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart mon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of East Germany I became the foster parent to all those kids you see photographed up on the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.70,0:07:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Foster parent yes well it just means that I took care of them until they were adopted or eventually able to go
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Go off on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy in the middle was adopted by the president of an accessories company
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.50,0:07:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last one on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.04,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is enlisted in the army
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.60,0:07:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have one left in my care right now and it must be hard work for you to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.98,0:08:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't call it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As the district official for the ministry of welfare I worked for many years dealing with orphans and I was Adam
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.19,0:08:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Easily against the way the government handled them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.31,0:08:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of socialism I thought I'd try doing things my own way
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.41,0:08:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do any worse
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.71,0:08:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it isn't easy and I don't have many resources
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.55,0:08:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's far better than the way they were living in that orphanage if you can call it that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The ministry of the interior and the ministry of welfare ran 511 kinderheim as a special or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.86,0:08:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well all these German orphanages were pretty severe places to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.26,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But these special orphanages were particularly notorious
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just an institution for children with nowhere to go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the place where children of criminals and political prisoners
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.53,0:08:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspected dissidents were sent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:08:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Discrimination and inhumane cruelty
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.88,0:09:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What part of everyday life for the children there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Those poor unfortunates were defenseless and couldn't do anything about their situation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.82,0:09:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ironically it was a contradictory clash between socialism
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.91,0:09:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And totalitarianism
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.50,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The government claim they were reeducating them to be good citizens but in actuality behind closed doors
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't away from the public eye those helpless children were treated like criminals even worse than criminals
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The director and instructors were absolutely terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.88,0:09:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst of the bunch would confiscate care packages sent to the children and sell them to their own profit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who then were the real criminals I ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear and violence rule the daily lives of those poor children and those special orphanages
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.96,0:09:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't raise normal people that way
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.82,0:09:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day that incident happened incident what exactly do you mean by that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:10:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well when you came here you said that you wanted to ask me about the twins didn't you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.09,0:10:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes that's right can you tell me anything at all about them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know much about the girl except that she was left at an orphanage in a different District but the boy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.56,0:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll always remember the brother Johan
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan yes please tell me whatever there is to know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.78,0:10:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened they kept everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,From finding out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.97,0:10:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The East German government placed a strict gag order on it well it is in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.37,0:10:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I suppose it's all right I guess there's no harm in talking to you about the incident so what are you talking
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.77,0:10:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking about I need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your hun too
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.98,0:10:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then uprising
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:10:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:10:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Diet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.94,0:11:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have company come here and say hello to him why don't you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.04,0:11:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Diet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are your manners
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well are you going to greet the man or not oh it's okay
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.44,0:11:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We already met earlier out in front of the building
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.26,0:11:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember
