Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.23,0:17:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is dark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.54,0:17:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The futures
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.94,0:17:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that isn't true
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.98,0:17:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's not a dark place that's a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.57,0:17:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Really
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.85,0:17:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes really
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.38,0:17:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh I almost forgot
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.69,0:17:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This soccer ball is for you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow will be a good day
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.60,0:17:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for coming so late thank you nurse
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.58,0:17:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But the ER is pretty busy at the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.89,0:17:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It might end up being a while before we can treat him
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't you move him up at all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a very big accident I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.82,0:17:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to ask the truck driver about the circumstances of the accident
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You broke both his legs but he can still talk any
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.48,0:17:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to treat him first
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can question him after we're done
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right then we'll wait right here until he's ready I see
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.93,0:18:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in 2 hours please just do what you can to take care of the boy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.33,0:18:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever you do please be sure not to let anyone else take him away I will be coming back to get him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.73,0:18:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe you one is the accident site cleaned up yet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.13,0:18:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Traffic still backed up okay what should I do now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First what to do with Dieter even if I call the police I can't go with him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.93,0:18:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know much about the girl except that she was left at an
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.33,0:18:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In a different District
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.63,0:18:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A different orphanage wait that's it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.43,0:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a child that you want me to take in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.78,0:19:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well are you the child's parent
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing coming here at this hour I'm sorry I know it's a strange request but this child needs you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.74,0:19:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Look I understand that the child is being abused
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.07,0:19:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I don't know who you are then how can I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.91,0:19:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just I can't take in a child from a suspicious person who won't even identify himself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.57,0:19:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.85,0:19:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Anna Liebert live here with you with this orphanage by any chance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.76,0:19:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that you know Anna Liebert
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.58,0:19:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.60,0:19:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do remember Anna
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes of course I do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Anna is she doing well for herself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.05,0:19:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She's currently taking classes at Heidelberg University
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Really then I guess she's doing very well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.22,0:19:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna was such a nice girl
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.26,0:19:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard she was adopted by Mr Liebert of the Commerce Ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.10,0:20:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with her twin brother
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.69,0:20:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name again Johan
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.99,0:20:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That was it his name was Johan they were truly very close I felt so sorry for them when they had to be separated but they
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to be placed in different orphanages
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.21,0:20:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the two of them arrived here they only had each other they were truly alone in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They were found walking hand in hand near the border of Czechoslovakia
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.24,0:20:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the two of them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.78,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Shivering all alone in the cold at first Mr Liebert was only going to adopt
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No hunts but Johan wouldn't go anywhere without his sister there was no separating them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully Anna was able to live a happy life because of her brother
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.65,0:20:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the conditions in the orphanages in East Germany were pretty terrible not all orphanages were like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.05,0:20:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,511 kinderheim
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Inga deer the bathroom is the other way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.46,0:21:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Down the hall okay
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right it's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right there's nothing to be afraid of now you can go to the bathroom by yourself can't you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.19,0:21:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These poor children have never really felt the love of a parent in order to develop as a person
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.59,0:21:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you need is love
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.38,0:21:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The orphanages of the East Side were truly horrible places for the children to grow up in everything was so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing personal even this place was only known by the number 47
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.88,0:21:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better believe we did everything we could do within our power so that we wouldn't be controlled by the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.28,0:21:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Pregnant we weren't going to be another 511 kinderheim it was a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.68,0:22:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Orphanage controlled by the ministry of welfare and the ministry of the Interior do you know what that means
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.62,0:22:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality was it was a Ministry of the Interiors Pet Project East Germany was using
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.02,0:22:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That place for experimentation on the children
